<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693472>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 4–9. Myolepta haemorrhoidalis (Philippi, 1865): (4) female visiting flowers of Crataegus sp., Cerro Isla Carlos Condell, Curicó (photo by Joaquín Sepulveda) and (5) dorsal view (photo by Patricia Henríquez). Scale bar = 1 mm. Myolepta luctuosus (Bigot, 1857): (6) female visiting Trevoa quinquenervia, Gillies & Hook, Rio Clarillo National Park (photo by Daniel Llavaneras) and (7) dorsal view (photo by Patricia Henríquez). Scale bar = 1 mm. Myolepta nausicaa (Hull, 1937): (8) dorsal view (photo by Kevin Moran, CNC) and (9) lateral view (photo by Kevin Moran, CNC). Scale bars = 2 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4693472/files/figure.png" .

